<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1047,1730,1757]" box="[151,1047,1730,1757]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1730,1756]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1867" box="[280,401,1730,1756]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Chalinidae</taxonomicName>
with unispicular secondary lines (from 
<bibRefCitation author="De Weerdt, W. H." box="[848,1035,1730,1757]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1867" refId="ref38764" refString="De Weerdt, W. H. (2002) Family Chalinidae Gray, 1867. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera: A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Vol. 1. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, New York, pp. 852 - 873. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 91" type="book chapter" year="2002">De Weerdt 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,557,1827,1854]" box="[151,557,1827,1854]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,557,1827,1854]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Grant, 1836" authorityName="Grant" authorityYear="1836" box="[279,557,1827,1854]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[279,400,1827,1854]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Haliclona</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, R. E." box="[407,557,1827,1853]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refId="ref39578" refString="Grant, R. E. (1836) Animal Kingdom. In: Todd, R. B. (Ed.), The Cyclopaedia of Anatomy and Physiology. Vol. 1. Sherwood, Gilbert, and Piper, London, pp. 107 - 118." type="book" year="1836">Grant, 1836</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1899,2034]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1899,1925]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Choanosomal skeleton consisting of a very regular, ladder-like reticulation of uni- to paucispicular primary lines, regularly connected by unispicular secondary lines. Ectosomal skeleton, if present, a unispicular tangential isotropic reticulation; occasionally with the oxeas ‘intercrossing’. Oxeas short, rather robust, fusiform or with acerate points. Spongin moderate to abundant (from 
<bibRefCitation author="De Weerdt, W. H." box="[797,985,2007,2034]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" pagination="1867" refId="ref38764" refString="De Weerdt, W. H. (2002) Family Chalinidae Gray, 1867. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; Van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera: A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Vol. 1. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, New York, pp. 852 - 873. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 1 - 4615 - 0747 - 5 _ 91" type="book chapter" year="2002">De Weerdt 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
